        <mxCell id="4mRV1LXF5f9laapuvszc-155" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Node2Vec/ Metapath2Vec Implementation&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;In a hybrid KG (with nodes either disease or phenotype), node2vec converts to both disease and hpo embeddings, while with metapath2vec specific node types can be defined to create vector embeddings.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14px;&quot;&gt;HPO Embeddings should be more reasonable when comparing to rare disease, than aggregating each phenotypes to one disease&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
